item.title: CVE-2019-3739|2024-09-16T17:43:20.591Z -- dell -- rsa%20bsafe%20crypto-j
item.description: RSA BSAFE Crypto-J versions prior to 6.2.5 are vulnerable to Information Exposure Through Timing Discrepancy vulnerabilities during ECDSA key generation. A malicious remote attacker could potentially exploit those vulnerabilities to recover ECDSA keys.
